<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1908-04-08T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1908-04-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="540" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d540">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Wilson</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Brussels</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1908-04-08"><hi rend="italic">April 8,
                                1908</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 323.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to transmit herewith
                            three copies of the proposed Kongo annexation bill<note n="1" xml:id="d540fn1">Not printed.</note> which has just been reported to
                            the Belgian Parliament by the committee of seventeen. I also transmit
                            three copies of the proposed bill for the government of the Belgian
                            colonial possessions reported by the same committee.</p>
                        <p>I have the honor, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Henry Lane
                            Wilson.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>